CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 2, 1960, pg. B3 reads: "Stoop 'N' Bend Garden Club held its 20th annual open meeting at the Pittsburgh Garden Center recently. A.E. Kimmerling of the City Bureau of Recreation and Parks was the speaker.  Pouring tea were Mmes. Edward Hale, Wilson Primas, Luke McDaniels and Clifford Morrison.  Mrs. Robert Mahoney was chairman, and Mrs. Charles Waters Jr. was co-chairman.  Above, seated : Mmes. Warren Tucker, Robert Mahoney, Charles Adams, president; Mary Randall, Lavinia Becker and Henry Patterson.  Standing: Mmes. Herbert Simmons, financial secretary; Harold Stoner, recording secretary; Charles Waters Jr., Henry Pope, second vice president; William Penn, Henri Vaughn, Leonard Hardy and Ulysses Williams. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Stoop 'n' Bend Garden Club members, from left, seated: Mrs. Warren Tucker, Mrs. Robert Mahoney, Mrs. Charles Adams, Mrs. Mary Randall, Mrs. Lavinia Becker, and Mrs. Henry Patterson; standing: Mrs. Herbert Simmons, Mrs. Harold Stoner, Mrs. Charles Waters Jr., Mrs. Henry Pope, Mrs. William Penn, Mrs. Henri Vaughn, Mrs. Leonard Hardy, and Mrs. Ulysses Williams, posed in park
